cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.LG, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new version of the Bang Calculus, a term language connecting CBPV and Linear Logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses a programming paradigm (CBPV) and presents a new calculus for it. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is another possible category as the paper provides a quantitative type system for the new calculus. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of a type system for CBN/CBV translations, which could be related to type systems used in machine learning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the properties of the new calculus and type system with respect to CBN/CBV translations, which could be relevant to software engineering.
